	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Aug 13th 4:27 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>309 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.18]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Just focus on the XP penalty--that is the advantage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherwise, you get caught in a circular loop that eventually a non-large, non-regen race is eventually going to lose.<br><br>It doesnt matter what race you are, unslowed PoP mobs WILL interrupt a vast majority of spells you try and cast if you are the MT.  Im interrupted all the damn time in those situations and I have all defensive AAs maxxed, channeling focus III AA, as well as 305 AGI.<br><br>Strength is a stat that is very important, but just too damn easy to increase to put any significant weight into it when choosing a race.<br><br>The impact on AGI and your ac is terrible and not even worth considering.  Talisman of the Wrulan, essentialy the best AGI buff out there, only adds like 6AC or so.<br><br>I would also caution insinuating that you chain lifetap throughout a fight.  On a raid, perhaps, but certainly not in a XP group for any significant length of time.  You will OOM yourself in a hurry, which is something you basically never want to do.  I dont care if you hav FT15 and C5 or not--oom will happen in a hurry.<br><br>Furthermore, while PoP has made a total mana pool more important then Luclin did, mana regen is still far more useful.  Hell, 3/4 of the time in PoP raids I cant cast as I want to anyways or else I will agro the mob in a hurry.  And you do NOT want to agro PoP bosses if you arent in the CH rotation.  They can essentially one round you in a HURRY.<br><br>As such, its an easy argument to make. The XP penalty is the answer--not a higher AGI, INT or whatever.  That is all fourplay and an argument a small race will lose every single time.  By the time the XP penalty advantage goes away, the gear that is available to you is greatly increased, minimizing the advantage of greater overall stats that the larger races enjoy at inception.<br><br>Luna<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Aug 13 16:20:13 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
